    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "A student wants to compare the horizontal positions of sad bees on screen. They want to calculate how far apart two bees are based on their x-locations.\r\n\r\n✅ <strong>TO DO:</strong> In <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">SadBeeScene.java</code>, write the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">getDistance()</code> method to return the distance between two <code>SadBee</code> objects. This method should:\r\n\r\n1. Take two <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">SadBee</code> objects as parameters.\r\n\r\n2. Use <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Math.abs()</code> to return the absolute value of the second bee’s x-location minus the first bee’s x-location.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #E0D1EC; border: 1px solid #9660bf; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1.1em; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">\r\n💡 <strong>TIP:</strong> Use <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Math.abs(second.getXLocation() - first.getXLocation())</code> to get the distance.\r\n</div>\r\n",
